 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm8","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: local_bridges graph-family rejection contracts diverge","description":"The wide parity matrix found local_bridges returns results on directed graphs and MultiGraph inputs where upstream NetworkX raises NetworkXNotImplemented.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z","close_reason":"Fixed: local_bridges raises NetworkXNotImplemented on directed and multigraph inputs, matching @not_implemented_for decorator.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm9","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: MultiGraph structural algorithms diverge from NetworkX","description":"The wide parity matrix found MultiGraph-specific structural gaps: is_tree and is_forest return true despite parallel edges where upstream returns false; bridges includes the parallel edge pair that upstream excludes; degree_centrality undercounts parallel-edge degree; complement raises TypeError where upstream returns a MultiGraph complement.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:48:54.137026Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T04:48:54.137026Z","close_reason":"Fixed in cycle-continuation commit: Python overrides for is_tree/is_forest/bridges/degree_centrality/complement on MultiGraph input match nx contract (count parallels, exclude parallel-edge bridges, delegate complement to nx for MG).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-nvupdt", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] G._node.update(...) crashes \u2014 nx.relabel_nodes / nx.convert_node_labels fail on fnx", "description": "nx.relabel._relabel_copy does H._node.update((n, d) for n, d in ...) \u2014 dict-style bulk insertion. fnx._node was aliased to the read-only NodeView which has no .update() method, causing AttributeError: NodeView object has no attribute update. As a result nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers and nx.relabel_nodes crashed when called on fnx graphs via the backend path. Fix: _node alias now returns a thin _PrivateNodeFacade dict-like that forwards reads to G.nodes and forwards bulk writes to G.add_node. Same behavior as a real dict for nx consumers.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T06:57:39.585486Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: _PrivateNodeFacade provides dict-style __getitem__/__setitem__/update/items/keys/values on top of the Rust NodeView + add_node. 5 regression tests in TestPrivateNodeFacadeUpdate cover nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers / nx.relabel_nodes on fnx.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T06:57:39.585486Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T06:57:39.585486Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-nxgraph", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] Cross-library constructor drops edges \u2014 fnx.Graph(nx.Graph) returns empty", "description": "fnx.Graph(nx.path_graph(3)) silently returned an empty graph because the Rust __new__ only knows fnx own graph types \u2014 for foreign (nx) graph instances it copies nodes but not edges. Fix: extend _init_absorbing_dict_of_dicts to detect foreign-graph sources and manually populate edges (with Multi*/simple collapse semantics per br-xmginit). fnx-native same-family sources still skip to avoid double-adding.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T07:07:28.042006Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-6.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:07:28.042006Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T07:07:28.042006Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-atlascp", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] AtlasView.copy() missing \u2014 breaks nx.to_dict_of_dicts on fnx graphs", "description": "nx.convert.to_dict_of_dicts does nbrdict.copy() on the adj value (which is fnx.AtlasView). AtlasView lacked the .copy() method, so the call crashed with AttributeError. Fix: add copy() returning a plain dict snapshot with attr dicts also materialized.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T07:07:28.042006Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-6.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:07:28.042006Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T07:07:28.042006Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
